title: South Region XC Rankings Includes Both Osprey Squads
text: South Region XC Rankings Includes Both Osprey Squads North Florida Athletics 10/20/2015 1:12:00 PM NEW ORLEANS, La . -- The USTFCCCA released its weekly Regional Cross Country Top 15 rankings with both North Florida teams on the South Region list as the Osprey men were ranked 9th and the women were 10th.The men's team is coming off a solid performances over the weekend having finished fifth at the competitive Crimson Classic in Tuscaloosa, Ala. Junior finished 16th overall running his second best time of the season, 25:00, over the 8k course.On the women's side, sophomore Eden Meyer was again the squad's top finisher running a 17:56 to finish 36th. As a team, UNF posted a ninth place finish in the 26-team field at the Crimson Classic. " The final poll of the regular season reflects that both men's and women's teams are moving up and it's nice to be trending that direction as the Atlantic Sun championships approaches," said head coach Jeff Pigg . "The women are coming off of a solid team performance in Alabama and we're certainly looking forward to the Atlantic Sun Championships. The women have gotten quite a bit better throughout the season and we look forward to continue to do that in the upcoming weeks. The men are continuing to battle through some injury and illness, but we feel are best meets are yet to come. This solid ranking and a strong performance in Alabama should have us well-positioned to perform very well at the conference championship."North Florida now sets its sights on the Atlantic Sun Championships, to be run Oct. 30 at UNF's home course, the Hayt Golf Learning Center.
